[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "1) Rare 2nd Moves"]
[Black "Odd queen moves  #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
{ The simplest way to respond most of those queen's moves is to play 3. d4 and transpose into the well-known lines or to play 3. Nc3 first, if necessary. However, I will mention possible ways to punish those queen moves. }
2... Qc7 3. c3
{ An attempt to punish Black.   The idea  3.d4  is the simplest.  3...cxd4  4.Nxd4  Nc6  5.Nc3  e6  transposes to the Taimanov variation which is part of our repertoire. }
3... Nf6 { If anything else White plays  4.d4  and gets the full centre. } 4.
e5 Nd5 5. c4
{ The white knight is going to c3 to attack the queen on c7 later. } 5... Nb4
{ Other knight jumps are bad for Black. } 6. Nc3 { White is ready to play d4. }
6... N4c6 7. Be2 { Developing and preparing to give away the pawn. } 7... e6
{ Black rejects 'the gift'. } 8. Nb5 Qb6 9. b4
{ White just wants to open up everything } 9... Nxb4
{ 9...cxb4?  is strategically lost after  10.d4  . } 10. a3 N4c6 11. Rb1
{ Attacking the queen indirectly. } 11... Qd8 12. Bb2
{ White has excellent attacking chances. There is some similarity in ideas with the 2...Nf6 line, and this is a much better version for White. }
*

