{ White has provoked f5 and now he goes back. The main point is that Nxd5 now is a much bigger threat than on move 5. }
6... Nc6 7. Nxd5 exd5 8. d4 { Proving that f5 is a serious weakness. } 8... d6
9. Bf4 { Fighting for the dark squares and an outpost on e5. } 9... cxd4 10.
exd6 Bxd6 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. Qd2 { Stopping Qb4+. } 12... Bd7 13. O-O-O a6 14.
Nxd4 O-O-O 15. f4
{ White has a nice edge due to the weakness on d5, the weak dark squares in Black's position and the better bishop. He can aim for the endgame with only bishops on the board. }
