[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2) Katalimov: 2...b6 / Nimzowitsch: 2..Nf6"]
[Black "Katalimov: 2...b6  #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 b6
{ From all playable Sicilians this one gives White the easiest play. Black wants to fianchetto his bishop as soon as possible, but there are few obvious drawbacks.   First, the 2...b6 move doesn't really fight for the centre, the pressure on the e4 is neglectable since White can easily defend the e4-pawn.   Secondly, when dealing against the kingside attack in Sicilian, Black always wants to create counterplay with b5-b4, which means that b7-b6 is practically a loss of tempo.   Finally, White has couple of promising lines @@StartBracket@@6. Bg5, 6. Bf4, 6. g3 , 6. Be3, 6. f3@@EndBracket@@ against it, but the 6. Bg5 is the most concrete one. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Bb7 5. Nc3 Nc6
{ Not very compatible with the b6-Bb7 setup. } 6. Bf4
{ Eyeing the weak diagonal in Black's position. 6. Bg5 is also a good developing move, but the text move is more concrete. }
6... a6
{ 6...Rc8  7.Nxc6!  and Black doesn't have a good way of recapturing.  7...Bxc6  runs into  8.Ba6  ,  7...dxc6  is strategically pointless and after  7...Rxc6  8.Bb5  followed by Qd3 and O-O-O White creates pressure on d7. }
7. Nxc6 Bxc6 8. Nd5
{ Black can't play Rc8 because the pawn on a6 is hanging @@StartBracket@@another drawback of the b6 move@@EndBracket@@, so he must give the light-squared bishop. }
8... Bxd5 9. Qxd5 Qc8 10. Qb3
{ Guarding the pawn on c2, attacking Black's pawn on b6 and removing the queen from potential attacks @@StartBracket@@Nf6 or e6@@EndBracket@@. }
10... b5 11. a4 { Undermining the weak pawns. } 11... b4
{ All Black's pieces are on the first rank and we are on move 12. } 12. Bd3
{ White now just plans to finish development. } 12... e6 13. a5
{ Fixing the a6 weakness. } 13... Ne7
{ The black knight is headed to the c6 square. } 14. Bd6
{ Attacking a pawn, and more importantly, forcing Black to lose the castling rights. }
14... Nc6 15. Bxf8 Kxf8 16. O-O f6 17. f4
{ White has the safer king, more space and no weaknesses which means he is much better. }
