9. exd5 Nf6 { Trying to be smart and collect the pawn on d5 with the knight. }
10. Bc4 b5 11. Bb3 Nxd5
{ If Black doesn't take the pawn, he is clearly worse. He lags in development and has weak light squares. }
12. Qf3
{ Unfortunately  12.Nf3  doesn't win because of  12...Nxe3  when the white queen is also hanging. }
12... e6
{ 12...Nxe3  13.fxe3!  the double threat remains  13...Ra7  14.Qxf7+  Kd8  15.O-O-O  with huge attacking chances for White. }
13. Bxd5 { Entering into a comfortable ending. } 13... Qxd5 14. Qxd5 exd5 15.
O-O-O Nc6 16. Ne2
{ White has a long-term advantage. He will collect the d5 pawn, while the other black pawn on d7 will remain weak forever. }
