Rfd1 { Black can't defend the d7-pawn since Bxb6 comes with a tempo. } 17...
hxg4 18. Rxd7 Nd4
{ Leads to simplification which favors White.   If  18...Nf5  then  19.Rc7!  and the rook on the seventh rank is a crucial factor. }
19. Bxd4 Kxd7 20. Bxe5+ Ke6 21. Bxh8 Rxh8 22. Bxa6 Nc6 23. Bc4+
{ White is a pawn up and his winning chances are much higher than Black's drawing chances. }
