{ 3...Nb4  14.Ne5  Nd5  transposes into 12...Nb4. } 14. a3
{ A typical move in the 'isolani' type of positions. White secures the b4-square in order to set up a battery on the b1-h7 diagonal. }
14... Rac8 { 14...f5  15.Bc2  leaves Black with a weakness on e6. } 15. g3
{ Or  15.Qd2  gives White easier play. 16.Rc1 and even 16.h4!? could be his next moves when Black deals with the Bf4 threat. }
