{ Pawns are fixed on the queenside which means that White should prepare for the kingside expansion. }
14. Bd3
{ White will guard c4 pawn with the b3. We are placing bishop on the b1-h7 diagonal to cover pawn on e4 and to prepare for the knight jump on d5. When Black recaptures on d5, White will take with e-pawn, opening the bishop. }
14... Bc6 15. Bc2 Nd7 16. Be3
{ Avoiding trade of the bishops to keep control of the g1-a7 diagonal. White will have free hands on the kingside. Black has no counterplay. }
