[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. e5 Nd5 7. Bd2 Nxc3 8.
bxc3 Bf8 { Is the admission of opening defeat in my opinion. } 9. Bd3 d6
{ After  9...Nc6  10.Nxc6  Black doesn't have a good way of recapturing. } 10.
Qe2 dxe5
{ Pressing too hard on e5 loses instantly  10...Nd7?  11.Nxe6  fxe6  12.Qh5+  and White wins queen. }
11. Qxe5 Qd6 12. Qe4
{ It makes sense to keep the queens when your opponent is lagging in development so much. The endgame after  12.Qxd6  Bxd6  13.Nb5  is also much better for White thanks to the bishop pair advantage. }
12... Nd7 13. Nb5 Qb8 14. Qc4 Nc5 15. Be3 a6 16. Bxc5 axb5 17. Qd4
{ White will take on b5 with the bishop, and the g7 is a much more important pawn for Black. His position might be lost already. }
