{ 7...d6  8.Qf3  White gets the favourable version of the   @@StartFEN@@r1b1kbnr/ppqp1ppp/2n1p3/8/3NP3/2N1B3/PPP2PPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6...a6  7.a3  Nf6  8.f4  variation, since a6 is more useful for Black than a3 is for White. This means that White has a very comfortable advantage.  8...Be7  9.O-O-O  O-O  We will have this position with  the a6 and a3 included also. Here, White reaction is a bit different.  10.Ndb5  Before playing g4 it is important to kick out the queen from c7 square.  10...Qb8  11.g4!  a6  12.Nd4  Nxd4  13.Bxd4  e5?  The only attempt for Black to punish  White which doesn't work well for him. Otherwise White will push g5.  14.g5!  Bg4  15.Qg3  exd4  16.gxf6  dxc3  17.h3!!  Brilliant move, White opens the h-file  17...Bxf6  18.hxg4  cxb2+  19.Kb1  Qc7  20.g5  White has a winning  attack since his king is much safer. }
