Nxc3 11. Bxc3
{ The most simplest way to recapture. By trading dark-squared bishops White will dominate on the dark squares. }
11... O-O 12. Qd2 f6
{ Black must activate his pieces, and move the d-pawn. Before that he needs to destroy the e5 pawn. }
13. exf6 Rxf6 14. g3 { Protecting pawn on f4. } 14... d5 15. Bxb4
{ White wants to leave light-squared bishops on the board. The most surprising fact for me is that Black has a very good statistics in this passive position. He is practically without any counterplay. }
