9... Nf6 10. Qg3 Qxg3 11. hxg3 e5
{ Sooner or later Black will have to play this move, so his bishop from c8 can breathe. }
12. f3 { Preparing g4, and securing the pawn on e4. } 12... Be6 13. a4
{ 13...b4  leaves a weak c4 square and the a-pawn, which means that Black is forced to move his rook. }
13... Rc8 14. Be2
{ 14.axb5  was played in the rapid game Grischuk - Harikrishna, Huaian 2017. White can always take on b5, and there is no need to hurry. }
14... Be7 15. axb5 axb5 16. Ra7
{ Black will have to move his bishop again if he wants to castle. In the meantime, White will play Kf2, place his rook to an open file, and improve his knight, preferably to d3 where it attacks e5 and c5. }
*

