5. Bd3
{ In this chapter we will check some rare variations, mostly pawn moves. } 5...
Qb6
{ Against all opening principles, Black still hasn't developed any light piece. }
6. Be3
{ Voluntarily offering the b2 pawn. The only problem White could have in this line is that he needs to remember many forced variations. If you succeed, in return you should get a winning position. }
6... Bc5 7. c3 { Defending the knight. } 7... Nc6
{ Instead of taking the poisoned pawn, Black attacks the knight on d4. } 8. Nd2
