9... Qxc3 10. Ne2 { 10.Nxc6  also wins by force, but it is more complex. }
10... Qe5
{ 10...Qxd3  11.Bxc5  Trading the bishops helps White to launch a deadly attack on the dark squares.  11...b6  12.Nf4  Before moving the bishop White gains some time.  12...Qb5  14.Be3!  Nf6  14.Rb1  The queen must be forced to lose control of the c4-square.  14...Qe5  15.Nc4  White is completely winning. }
11. Nc4 Qh5 12. Qc1 Bxe3 13. Qxe3
{ Black position is so bad, that his best option is to give up the piece. }
13... Nf6 14. Ng3 Qxh2+ 15. Kxh2 Ng4+ 16. Kg1 Nxe3 17. Nxe3
{ White should convert the extra piece. } *

