[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6
{ The Kan Variation. Black delays Nc6 and keeps the knight on b8 flexible. Also, the knight doesn't stand in way and blocks the queen on c7 or the bishop on b7 afterward.   This point can be seen best if White tries to deploy a typical English attack.  5.Nc3  Qc7  6.Be3?!  Bb4  7.Qd2?!  Nf6  8.f3  d5  where Black already has a more pleasant position.   The drawback of the move  4...a6  is that it doesn't develop anything nor fights for the centre. Therefore, White's best choices are the positional  5.c4  and the concrete and more flexible  5.Bd3  which I'm recommending. }
5. Bd3
{ In this chapter we will check some rare variations, mostly pawn moves. } 5...
Qb6
{ Against all opening principles, Black still hasn't developed any light piece. }
6. Be3
{ Voluntarily offering the b2 pawn. The only problem White could have in this line is that he needs to remember many forced variations. If you succeed, in return you should get a winning position. }
6... Qxb2
{ If Black wants to take that pawn, he should take it as soon as possible.   6...Nf6  7.Nd2  Qc7  Is just too deep for my understanding of chess.  8.O-O  Be7  9.f4  O-O  10.g4  Give White excellent attacking chances compared to the Scheveningen lines. White is about 4-5 tempi faster. }
7. Nd2 Qc3
{ 7...Nc6?!  8.Rb1  Qa3  9.Nxc6  dxc6  10.e5  As usual Black is undeveloped and has too many weak squares in his camp. }
8. O-O Qc7
{ Black must take the queen to a safe place to cover all the weaknesses. } 9.
e5 { Another 'pawn sacrifice' which prevents Black from developing. } 9... Ne7
10. Nc4 Nd5 11. a4 { Stopping b5 and securing the knight on c4. } 11... Nxe3
{ 11...Nc6  12.Nxc6  Qxc6  13.a5  Paralyzes Black's queenside. } 12. fxe3 d5
13. exd6 Bxd6 14. Nxd6+ Qxd6
{ Black is one move away from safety @@StartBracket@@a.k.a. castle@@EndBracket@@, but White can stop it. }
15. Nb5 Qe5 16. Nd6+ { Winning the queen. } 16... Qxd6 17. Bb5+
{ Discovered check! } 17... Ke7 18. Rxf7+ { Deflection. } 18... Kxf7 19. Qxd6
axb5 20. Rf1+ Ke8 21. axb5
{ Material is roughly equal, but Black is completely paralyzed and his king is weak. White will collect a few pawns @@StartBracket@@e6, g7, h7@@EndBracket@@ and that should bring him the victory. }
*

