9. Nxc6 dxc6 10. a4 { Stopping b5. } 10... e5 11. Nd2 Bg4
{ Before playing Be6 Black provokes f3 first. } 12. f3 Be6 13. a5 O-O 14. Nc4
{ Taking the bishop pair. } 14... Bxc4 15. Bxc4 Qe7 16. c3
{ White has a stable bishop pair advantage, but Black's position is very solid. }
