{ White finally plays c4 and aims for the setup Nc3-Bd2-f4-Kh1-Rae1 with the e5 and f5 pawn breaks. }
8... g6 9. Nc3 Bg7 10. Be3 { The simplest possible way for White to play. }
10... O-O 11. Rac1 Nbd7
{ Going for the classical hedgehog setup.   11...Nc6  The knight on c6 attracts some trouble on the c-file for Black.  12.Rfd1  Bd7  13.Nxc6  bxc6  Black must recapture with the pawn due to Nd5  14.b4  Rfb8  15.a3  White has a space advantage and can slowly improve his position. }
