{ 9...g6?!  10.f5!  Ne5  11.Nf3  Asks a lot of questions about Black's opening concept. }
10. Qe2 Be7
{ White can play  11.Kh1  to transpose to the next chapter, or try the ambitious text move. }
11. f5 e5 12. Nb3
{ White is better thanks to the space advantage and the attacking chances on the kingside. He should stop any counterplay connected with b5, by playing a4, and prepare for g4-g5. }
