6. O-O d6
{ 6...Bc5  7.Nb3  Bd6  Not a great square for the bishop, but the only one that stops e5.  8.f4  e5  9.Nc3  O-O  10.Nd5!  Opens up White's bishop.  10...Nxd5  11.exd5  g6  12.c4  b6  13.Qe2  Re8  14.fxe5  Black's queenside is chronically undeveloped.   6...Qb6  7.Be3!  is a transposition to 5...Qb6 6.Be3. }
