8. Nc3 Bb7
{ Developing the c8-bishop first, before castling is a bit dubious and you will see why.   Probably Black should play  8...Be7  9.f4  O-O  10.Qe2  and transpose into the main lines. }
9. f4 g6
{ Black should play  9...Nbd7  or  9...Be7  . This move really invites trouble. }
10. f5 gxf5 11. exf5 Rg8
{ Has been played surprisingly a lot since it looks extremely dubious. } 12.
Rf2
{ White players were usually choosing  12.Ne4  but there is a stronger move. }
12... e5
{ 12...Ng4  13.fxe6  Nxf2  14.exf7  Kxf7  15.Qh5  White wins back everything. }
13. Ne6 fxe6 14. fxe6
{ This was in fact a positional piece sacrifice. White has many powerful threats that Black can't parry. }
14... Qe7 15. Bf5 Qg7 16. Nd5 Be7 17. Be3
{ If Black takes on d5, he will open the c-file for a white rook. } 17... Nc6
{ The only way for Black to continue the development. } 18. Nxf6+ Bxf6 19. Qh5+
Kd8 20. Bh6 Qe7 21. Be4
{ Depending on the next black move White will play 22. Qf7 or 22. Raf1 and pick up the bishop on f6. }
*

