e5 11. Bxa7 Rxa7 12. Nc3 { White's moves are very simple. } 12... O-O
{ Black can play  12...b6  first, but that move hardly has any independent value after  13.Qe3  and Rfd1. }
13. Qe3 Be6 14. Rfd1 b6
{ Black should take advantage of the rook being on a7 instead of returning it to a8.   14...Ra8  15.Bf1  Rc8  16.h3  Nb8  17.Nd2  Nbd7  18.a3  White has nice potential on the queenside. }
15. Bf1 Qb8
{ The best square for the black queen, it guards b6 and d6, and doesn't block the a7-rook. }
16. Rac1
{ White is slightly better thanks to the weakness on the d6 and d5-square. } *

