7... Bb4 8. Bd2 O-O
{ Alternatives are barely worth of mentioning or have no independent value. }
9. a3
{ Now Black has to decide, to give up the bishop or admit the 'mistake' and pretend it was all part of the plan to provoke a3. }
9... Be7
{ A few decades ago, the move a3 in connection with an English Attack setup was considered as a weakness, but modern day engines are teaching us the opposite. Which explains why this line is nowadays rarely seen at grandmaster level. }
10. O-O-O Qc7 { isn't much flexible, White just starts advancing pawns. } 11.
f4 a6 12. g4 d5 13. g5 { Forcing exchanges on e4. } 13... Nxe4 14. Nxe4 dxe4
