{ Since the classical English attack setup @@StartBracket@@Be3, Qd2@@EndBracket@@ runs into Bb4 followed by a quick d5 White has to be more subtle. The text move is known as the right antidote to the Qb6 line. White is preparing to play e5. }
7... Bb4 8. Bd2 O-O
{ Alternatives are barely worth of mentioning or have no independent value. }
9. a3
{ Now Black has to decide, to give up the bishop or admit the 'mistake' and pretend it was all part of the plan to provoke a3. }
9... Be7
{ A few decades ago, the move a3 in connection with an English Attack setup was considered as a weakness, but modern day engines are teaching us the opposite. Which explains why this line is nowadays rarely seen at grandmaster level. }
10. O-O-O d5 11. e5
{ The pawn structure has been changed and resembles the 'French defence', but inferior for Black. }
11... Ne8 12. f4 f6 13. Be3 Qd8
{ The queen is not happier on the initial square. } 14. exf6 Bxf6 15. Ne4
{ And White will take the dark-squared bishop. } *

