12... Be7
{ This move has been played most often.   12...Rb8  13.Qf2  b4  14.Na4  transposes to 12...b4. }
13. h4 { 13.Qf2  and  13.Kb1  are equally good options. } 13... b4 14. Na4 Bb7
15. Qf2 { As usual White fights for the b6 square. } 15... Na5
{ Opening the queen and the bishop simultaneously. } 16. Nb6
{ Forcing trades of knights. I chose this line as an example why White has stronger attack. }
16... Nxb3+ 17. axb3 Nxb6 18. Bxb6 Qc6 19. Bd3
