13... Nbd7 14. O-O-O h6
{ Black has to be very careful when playing h6 since it creates a hook for White @@StartBracket@@g4, h4, g5@@EndBracket@@. }
15. Be3 h5 16. h3 O-O-O 17. Ba7
{ Taking away the b8 square. Very strong play by the Chinese GM. } 17... Nc5
18. Bb6 Rde8 19. Bxc5 { The right time for exchange. } 19... dxc5 20. d6
{ was strategically winning for White in Yu Yangyi - Li Chao, Ningbo 2018. } *

