{ Here we have another branching point. Black can play  7...b5  to stop  8.Nc4  or he can play some developing move:   a@@EndBracket@@  7...Nf6  ,   b@@EndBracket@@  7...Be6  and   c@@EndBracket@@  7...Be7  . }
7... Be6 8. Nc4 { Improving our worst piece. } 8... Be7 9. Be3 Nf6 10. Nb6
{ Fixing the queenside and controlling the d5-square. } 10... Rb8 11. Be2
{ Developing and stopping Ng4. } 11... Nxe4
{ A tactical resource which isn't enough for equality. } 12. Nxe4 d5 13. Nc5
{ Counterattacking. } 13... d4 14. Nxe6 fxe6
{ We have spoiled Black's pawn structure, and it's time for some simple chess. }
15. Nc4 dxe3 16. Nxe3 { White has the better pawn structure. } *

