13... Na5 { Going to c4, but White is ready to trade bishops for knights. } 14.
Bg5 { With the obvious idea to capture on f6 and jump on d5. } 14... Nc4 15.
Bxc4 { This knight needs to be destroyed. } 15... bxc4 16. Rb1
{ The pawn was hanging and needs to be protected. } 16... Qc6
{ 16...Nd5  tactics give White what he wants:  17.Nxd5  Bxg5  18.O-O  with a typical advantage @@StartBracket@@a better knight vs. a bad bishop@@EndBracket@@. }
17. Bxf6 { Eliminating the knight who guards the d5 square. } 17... Bxf6 18.
O-O
