{ 12.a4  Nb4  is the reason behind move Rb8. White makes a semi-waiting move instead.   He has some other possibilities as well, such as  12.a3  , while  12.Ncd5  is too early because of  12...Nxd5  13.Nxd5  Bg5  when rook on b8 proves to be very useful.   It needs to be said that Re1 creates an extra square for white bishop on f1. }
12... Nd4 13. b3
{ Another useful waiting move.   13.a4  is too early  13...b4  14.Ncd5  Nxd5  15.Nxd5  Bg5  and Black might be fine. }
13... Kh8
{ Black is also waiting.  13...Ne6  or  13...Bd7  are both answered by  14.a4  . }
14. Bd2 { White's moves are more useful than the black ones. } 14... Ne6 15.
Ncd5 { Now it is the perfect time to jump. } 15... Nxd5 16. Nxd5 Nc5 17. Bb4
{ White has an edge because of a weak pawn on d6. } *

