14. Qa3
{ Still keeping the c5 option alive, and the queen on b3 runs into a tempo after a4. }
14... Be7 15. O-O-O O-O 16. Kb1
{ Black can't play b5 easily without losing a pawn, which means that he can hardly attack the white king. On the other hand, White can try to crash through the kingside, or through the centre. }
