12. Be2 { Prevents some desperate sacrifices on f3 and c3 followed by Nxe4. }
12... Nc4 13. Bxc4 Rxc4 14. h4
{ White is clear tempo up compared to the line arising from 9. Bc4 where he has advantage anyway. Here, his attack is just winning. }
