15... Qd7 16. Rg1
{ When the opponent knight is on h5, the rook belongs to the g-file. } 16... a6
17. Nc3 { White has successfully provoked a6 and created a hole on b6. } 17...
Bxd4 18. Qxd4 b5 19. Rg5 { Rxh5 ideas are in the air. } 19... Nf6 20. Nd5 Bxd5
21. exd5 { White has opened the long diagonal for his bishop. } 21... Qc7 22.
Bd3 Qc5 23. Qf4 { Black's kingside will collapse soon. } *

