12. h4 { White's moves are simple. } 12... Rfc8 13. h5
{ Logical continuation of previous moves. } 13... Qa5 14. hxg6 fxg6
{ This recapture is probably a bit safer for Black's king, but on the other hand it leaves him without counterplay. }
15. a3 Rab8 16. Qe3
{ A double attack: a7 is hanging and e5 is a strong threat. Other moves such as  16.Qe1  ,  16.g4  or  16.Bd3  also give White a winning advantage, but this one is the strongest. }
16... Bf7 { Aimed against e5. } 17. Nb5 b6 18. Bc3
{ White wins an exchange, because black's queen has no good squares. } *

