12. h4 { White's moves are simple. } 12... Rfc8 13. h5
{ Logical continuation of previous moves. } 13... Qa5 14. hxg6 hxg6
{ Black can't really sacrifice an exchange on c3 since the White king will have an escape route via d2. }
15. a3 { Before continuing the attack, prophylaxis. } 15... Rab8 16. Bd3
{ Connecting the rooks, covering c2, and eyeing g6. } 16... Bc4 17. Bxc4 Rxc4
18. Qf2 { Anticipating e7-e5. } 18... Rbc8 19. Rd3
{ White first consolidates his queenside in instead of carelessly continuing with the attack. }
