12... Bxd4
{ This move was recommended by Gawain Jones in his books about the Dragon. Until recently @@StartBracket@@read Anish Giri's Dragon course@@EndBracket@@, the whole line has been considered as the best option for Black. }
13. Qxd4 Qc7 14. h4
{ White rarely takes pawn@@StartBracket@@s@@EndBracket@@ in this line, it is better for him to continue with the attack. }
14... Nf4 15. Qe3 Rb8 16. b3 { Preparing for Rd4. } 16... Be6 17. Rd4 Nd5 18.
Nxd5 cxd5 19. Bd3 Rfc8 20. h5 Qc3
{ Only looks dangerous for White, but Black has nothing. } 21. Kb1
{ The pawn on d5 only helps White. } 21... Rc4 22. Rdh4 Rxh4 23. Rxh4
{ White has better attacking chances, and better endgame also. } *

