Qc7
{ More popular than  14...Qa5  , although it is hard to say which move is the better one for Black. }
15. Bc4 Nb6
{ This move is completely underestimated. It was first played in 2015. by Nakamura, but hasn't found much supporters. White should never open the a-file, therefore next move is logical. }
16. Bb3 Nxa4 17. Qxa4 c5 18. Rhe1 e6 19. Qe4 Ba6
{ We were following the game Caruana-Nakamura, FIDE GP 2015. } 20. Qe5
{ Fabi played  20.Bxe6  which simplifies the position too much. } 20... Qxe5
21. Rxe5 Rfc8 22. Rd6 Bf1 23. g4
{ White is certainly on the top, but with precise play Black can hold this endgame. }
