18. h5 Nb6 19. Bxb6
{ The most forcing move, going for a slightly better endgame with bishops of opposite colour. }
19... Rxd2
{ The best chance for Black is to trade queens since his king is weaker. } 20.
Bc4+ Kf8 21. Bxc7 Rxd1+ 22. Rxd1 Rxc7
{ The position has been drastically simplified, with only bishop + rook pairs remaining on the board. Black pawns are weaker. }
23. hxg6 Bh6+ 24. Kb1 hxg6 25. Rd6 Kg7
{ Up to this moment, we were following the forcing line which is recommended by Giri in his Dragon course. White here has many ways to continue. Objectively, Black should draw this endgame, but the real question is how many players in the world can hold it. }
26. Re6
{ Not the only move for White, but it prevents e4. Other interesting options are  26.c3  ,  26.a4  ,  26.b4  ... }
