8. Qd2 { White now  goes for the typical English attack setup. } 8... Be7 9.
O-O-O O-O 10. g4
{ White has  castled and is ready to push the kingside pawns. This is the most classical  position in the whole Sicilian. }
10... Nd7 11. h4 Nde5
