{ 12.Qg2  is also very promising, but now is the perfect time to capture on c6. }
12... bxc6 13. Be2
{ White is ready to push the f-pawn and kick out the knight from e5. Black can't create much counterplay on the b-file. We had a similar pawn structure in the Taimanov variation, and this is a better version of it. }
13... Rb8 14. f4 Nd7 15. h5 { White has a much stronger attack. } *

