{ The kingside pawns are not important. } 17... Ne5 18. Qxf4 Nfxg4 19. Kb1
{ We won't blunder the queen. } 19... O-O { Black finally castles. } 20. h3
{ White will now occupy the g-file. } 20... Nf6 21. Bb6 { Gaining time. } 21...
Qd7 22. Rg1 { Another useful move which comes with a tempo. } 22... Kh8 23.
Qxb4 { Regaining material. The bshop pair is dominant is such positions. } *

