Be7 9. Qd2 O-O 10. O-O-O b5 11. g4 b4
{ Black should avoid this move.  11...Nbd7  is better and a transposition to the main line. }
12. Nd5 Bxd5 13. exd5 { White got the bishop  pair advantage for nothing. }
13... a5 14. Kb1 { Securing the kingside. } 14... a4 15. Nc1 Qa5
{ 15...Ra5?  played in more than 25 games! Loses immediately  16.Qxb4!  White properly reacted only twice  16...Nxd5  17.Rxd5!  the point  17...Rxd5  18.Bc4  and White is completely winning. }
16. g5 Nfd7 17. h4
{ White has a faster attack and domination on the light squares. } *

