{ Black can't play this position without the move Nbd7. } 11. Qd2 g6
{ 11...Be7  12.O-O-O  or   11...Qc7  12.O-O-O  would transpose into theBe6-Be7-h5 line. }
12. O-O-O
{ More direct than the positional  12.Be2  .   12...b5?  is premature,  13.Na5!  Nb6   13...Bg7  allows White to play both  14.c4  and Nc6 with a huge advantage.  14.Qc3!  the crushing move. 15. Qc6 is the strong idea, and Black is in trouble. }
12... Qc7
{ Or  12...Bg7  13.Kb1  when Black doesn't have anything better than transpose to 12...Qc7. }
