1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. f3 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. Be3
Be7 { or  8...h5  9.Qd2  Be7  . } 9. Qd2 h5 10. Be2
{ The main line is  10.Nd5  which is heavily covered in Anish Giri's Najdorf course. With the Be2 move White is aiming to obtain the bishop-pair advantage. }
10... Nbd7 11. Nd5 { Now it is time to jump. } 11... Nxd5 12. exd5 Bf5 13. O-O
{ 13.Na5  would allow Black to include a check on h4 and weaken white's kingside  13...Bh4+  14.g3  Bf6  . }
13... O-O 14. Na5 { Once this knight lands on a5, White has a nice advantage. }
14... Qc7 15. c4
{ White enjoys a nice advantage here. The plan is b4, Rac1, Rfd1 and pushing c5 at the right moment. }
