22. hxg6 hxg6 { 22...fxg6  23.Rhc1  Leaves Black with a bad pawn structure. }
23. cxb5 axb5 24. Rbc1
{ White found a hidden tactical resource. Rxc3 with Bd4 is a huge threat. }
24... b4
{ White has a connected passed pawn, and Black has no counterplay. White is positionally winning. }
25. Rh4 { The best square for the white rook. } 25... Ra5 26. Bd4
{ Forcing the exchange of bishops. } 26... Bxd4 27. Rxc8+ Bxc8 28. Rxd4
{ White will have two outside connected pawns. } 28... Bb7 29. Bb5
{ The most precise. Keeping the pawn on d5 alive. } 29... Ra8 30. Kd3 Rc8 31.
Rc4 Rb8 32. Kd4 e5+ 33. dxe6 fxe6 34. Rxb4
{ White has picked up a pawn, and the rest is easy. } 34... Bd5 35. Kc3 Kf7 36.
