1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. e5 Nd5 8.
Ne4 Qc7 9. f4 Qb6 10. c4 Bb4+ 11. Ke2 f5 12. exf6 Nxf6 13. Be3 Qd8 14. Nd6+
Bxd6 15. Qxd6 Bb7 16. Rd1 Rc8 17. Rg1 c5 18. g4 Qc7 19. g5 Ne4 20. Qe5
{ Up to here everything is mentioned in thecourse. } 20... d6
{ Black sacrifices a pawn since taking on e5 is not very appealing to him. }
21. Qxe6+ Kd8 22. g6
{ Important move, which keeps white queen active. Black was threatening Re8 which would give him a strong play over the e-file. }
22... Re8
{ 22...hxg6  23.Bg2  Qd7   23...Re8?  24.Qxg6  24.f5  Rxh2  25.Bf4  Rxg2+ } 23.
gxh7 { The point of playing g6. White loses queen but gets a new one instead. }
23... Rxe6 24. h8=Q+ Re8 25. Qxg7
{ White is two pawns up, although Black has some compensation because white king is weak. }
25... Qb6 { Rc7 is a big threat. } 26. Rg6 Rc7 27. Rgxd6+ Nxd6 28. Qf6+ Kc8 29.
Rxd6 Qb4
{ Mistake which loses directly.   29...Rc6  The only move for Black who has to exchange one pair of rooks.  30.Rxc6+  Bxc6  31.Kf2  Bd7!  Engines claim that Black can hold this position, but it certainly doesn't look pleasant for him. Endgame with 3 pawns down rarely brings a positive result. }
30. Bh3+ Kb8 31. Be6
{ White loses a lot of advantage with this move.   31.Rd8+!  Rxd8  32.Qxd8+  Bc8  33.b3!  Was the most precise execution. Plan is to push the f-pawn. For example  33...Qa3  34.Kf3  Qxa2  35.f5!  Kb7  36.Bg2  Bd7  37.Kg3+  Bc6  38.Bxc6+  Rxc6  39.Qd3!  Not an easy sequence, but it seems that White king is safe on g3. }
31... Bc8 32. b3 Qa3
{ 32...Qb7!  Was the only move again. Black defends the queenside prepares to infiltrate via g2 square. }
33. f5 Qxa2+ 34. Rd2 Qb1 35. Rd8 Qc2+ 36. Kf3 Rxd8 37. Qxd8 Qxb3 38. f6
{ The f-pawn is too strong. } 38... Rc6 39. Bxc8 Rxc8 40. Qd5
{ 40.Qd6+  Ka8  41.Qd5+  Wins on the spot. } 40... Re8 41. Qd6+ Kc8 42. Qxc5+
Kd8 { 42...Kd7!  43.Qxa7+  Ke6!  is a surprising draw. } 43. Qd4+ Kc8 44. h4
Qb7+ 45. Qd5 Qxd5+ 46. cxd5 Rf8
{ The final mistake.   46...Kd7!  47.Bc5  Re1!  Draws. } 47. Bd4 Kd7 48. Kf4
Ke8 49. Ke5 Kf7 50. d6 Re8+ 51. Kd5 Rd8 52. h5 a5 53. h6 a4 54. h7 a3 55. Kc6
Rc8+ 56. Kb7 Rh8 57. d7 *

