15. Bxb4 Nxb4 16. Nd4 { Not blundering Nxc2. } 16... Qb6 17. c3 Nc6 18. O-O-O
{ White is having a risk free advantage. Black has no counterplay and his position is extremely passive. }
18... Bd7 { So far we have been following the theoreticalchapter. } 19. Be2
