{ White enjoys a big risk free advantage in the endgame thanks to the better pawn structure and better bishop. }
22... Bg6 23. Bf3 Bf7 24. Rd3 h6 25. Re1 Rc8 26. Re5 Rc4 27. b3 Rc7 28. Kd2 Kf8
29. h4 { The usual play from the White side. } 29... Be8 30. Rd4 Bc6 31. a4
{ Gaining space more and more. } 31... Rd7
{ Unfortunate square for the rook.   31...a5!?  Prevents White from occupying more space. }
32. g4 Rdf7 33. Ke3 Ke7 34. c4
{ White transforms his advantage into the winning rook endgame. } 34... dxc4
